<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38163c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38163c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38163c"> 163(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> body, soul, shade, / shadow &amp; heart ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But, as according to the cult of Ra, the wicked, the rebels, and the blasphemers of the Sun-god suffered swift and final punishment, so also all those who had sinned against the stern moral Law of Osiris, and who had failed to satisfy its demands, paid the penalty without delay. The Judgment of Ra was held at sunrise, and the wicked were thrown into deep pits filled with fire, and their <mark>bodies, souls, shadows and hearts</mark> were consumed forthwith. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 21</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
